The Department of State Services, DSS, has warned “unpatriotic elements” against actions that threaten Nigeria’s security and unity. DSS Director-General, Yusuf Bichi warned that the secret police would ensure the unity and corporate existence of Nigeria. Bichi issued the warning at the graduation ceremony for participants of the Executive Intelligence Management Course at the National Institute for Security Studies in Abuja, on Saturday. He said: “We must not let selfish people with greedy interest destroy our collective heritage. “We must not allow unpatriotic elements to bring our country down. So, let us unite individually and collectively to address our challenges, and build a better nation for ourselves, our children and their generation. “We all have contributions to make in ensuring that Nigeria becomes safe, peaceful and developed. “The criticisms about the security agencies; people don’t appreciate where we were, and where we are now.”